               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-805" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-805" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-805" type="surname" value="MYERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-805" type="given" value="ANDREW"></interp>ANDREW MYERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Dorrington-street, Clerkenwell. About three o'clock, on the 23rd of March, I was opposite my shop, and saw the prisoner kneeling down by my shop window, reaching into the shop—he took something down, and concealed it under his coat—I followed, and called "Stop thief"—he ran—I saw him drop the telescope—I picked part of it up, and a boy picked up the remainder—this now produced is it, and here is the string it hung by.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-806" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-806" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-806" type="surname" value="BRANNAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-806" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BRANNAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a police-sergeant. I heard a cry of "Stop thief," and stopped the prisoner—he pointed forward, and said, "Them he goes"—a boy picked up part of the telescope and gave it to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I never had the telescope; I was walking along the gentleman collared me, and said, "Where are you running to?" I said, "Up here."</p>
